le=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|Japan}} Kimio Hirano\n|TKO\n|8 (12)\n|May 19, 1991\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|{{flagicon|Japan}} Kusanagi Gymnasium, [[Shizuoka (city)|Shizuoka]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture]], Japan}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Retained WBC and lineal minimumweight titles}}\n|-\n|27\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|27\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|Japan}} [[Hideyuki Ohashi]]\n|TKO\n|5 (12)\n|Oct 25, 1990\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|{{flagicon|Japan}} [[Korakuen Hall]], [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Won [[list of WBC world champions#Minimumweight|WBC]] and lineal minimumweight titles}}\n|-\n|26\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|26\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Francisco Montiel\n|UD\n|10 (10)\n|Jun 29, 1990\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|{{flagicon|MEX}} Mexico City, Mexico}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n|-\n|25\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|25\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Jorge Rivera\n|KO\n|8 (12)\n|Mar 15, 1990\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Fairmont Hotels and Resorts|Fairmont Hotel]], [[Dallas]], [[Texas]], [[United States]]}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Retained WBC Continental Americas Minimumweight title.}}\n|-\n|24\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|24\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Rey Hernandez\n|KO\n|12 (12)\n|Nov 7, 1989\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|{{flagicon|MEX}} [[Arena M\u00e9xico]], Mexico City, Mexico}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Won [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] Continental Americas [[Mini flyweight|Minimumweight]] title.}}\n|-\n|23\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|23\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Jose Luis Zepeda\n|TKO\n|7 (10)\n|Aug 26, 1989\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|{{flagicon|MEX}} Mexico City, Mexico}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n|-\n|22\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|22\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} Raymundo Ricardo Mendoza\n|KO\n|5\n|Aug 4, 1989\n|style=\"text-alig