 Darcy, Countess Rivers\n|28= 28. John Savile, 1st Baron Savile of Pomfret\n|29= 29. Elizabeth Cary\n|30= 30. Christopher Villiers, 1st Earl of Anglesey\n|31= 31. Elizabeth Sheldon\n}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Chichester (UK Parliament constituency)|Member for Chichester]] | with=[[Sir Thomas Miller, 3rd Baronet|Sir Thomas Miller]] | years=1722\u20131723 | before=[[Sir Thomas Miller, 3rd Baronet|Sir Thomas Miller]] | before2=[[Henry Kelsall]] | after=[[Sir Thomas Miller, 3rd Baronet|Sir Thomas Miller]] | after2=[[Lord William Beauclerk]]}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef | before=[[Algernon Seymour, 7th Duke of Somerset|The Duke of Somerset]]}}\n{{s-ttl | title=Colonel of the [[Royal Horse Guards]] | years=1750}}\n{{s-vac | next=[[John Ligonier, 1st Earl Ligonier|Sir John Ligonier]]}}\n{{s-npo|mason}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Premier Grand Lodge of England|Grand Master of the Premier<br />Grand Lodge of England]] | before=[[Francis Scott, 2nd Duke of Buccleuch|The Duke of Buccleuch]] | after=[[James Hamilton, 7th Earl of Abercorn|Lord Paisley]] | years=1724\u20131725}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box|title=[[Master of the Horse]]|before=[[Richard Lumley, 2nd Earl of Scarbrough|The Earl of Scarbrough]]|after=Vacant|years=1735\u20131750}}\n{{s-reg|en}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Charles Lennox, 1st Duke of Richmond|Charles Lennox]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Duke of Richmond]]|creation=3rd creation|years=1723\u20131750}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Charles Lennox, 3rd Duke of Richmond|Charles Lennox]]}}\n{{s-reg|sct}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Charles Lennox, 1st Duke of Richmond|Charles Lennox]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Duke of Lennox]]|creation=2nd creation|years=1723\u20131750}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Charles Lennox, 3rd Duke of Richmond|Charles Lennox]]}}\n{{s-reg|fr}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Charles Lennox, 1st Duke of Richmond|Charles Lennox]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Duke of Aubigny]]|years=1723\u20131734}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Charles Lennox, 3rd Duke of Richmond|Charles Lennox]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{PGLE}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Richmond, Charles Lennox, 2nd Duke Of}}\n[[Category:1701 births]]\n[[Category:1750 deaths]]\n[[Category:British Army generals]]\n[[Category:British Army personnel of the Jacobite rising of 1745]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1722\u20131727|March, Charles Lennox, Earl of]]\n[[Category:Mayors of places in West Sussex]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Richmond|302]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Lennox|202]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Aubigny]]\n[[Category:Earls of March (1675)|Charles]]\n[[Category:English cricketers of 1701 to 1786]]\n[[Category:English cricketers]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:Knights Companion of the Order of the Bath]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Garter]]\n[[Category:Sussex cricketers]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies|March, Charles Lennox, Earl of]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Royal Horse Guards officers]]\n[[Category:Burials at Chichester Cathedral]]\n[[Category:Cricket patrons]]\n[[Category:Grand Masters of the Premier Grand Lodge of England]]\n[[Category:Freemasons of the Premier Grand Lodge of England]]\n[[Category:18th-century philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Society of Antiquaries of London]]\n", "name_user": "Wilfridselsey", "label": "safe", "comment": "sp", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Lennox,_2nd_Duke_of_Richmond"}
{"title_page": "Celeste (Celeste album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Celeste\n| type         = Studio\n| artist       = [[Celeste (singer)|Celeste]]\n| cover        = Celeste - Celeste.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|09|04|df=yes}}\n| genre        = <!--Please source genre-->\n| length       = \n| label        = [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Jamie Hartman]]|[[John Hill (record producer)|John Hill]]|Barney Lister|Swindle|[[Stephen Wrabel]]}}\n| prev_title   = Lately\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| year         = 2020\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Celeste\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Strange (Celeste song)|Strange]]\n | single1date = 9 April 2019\n | single2     = [[Stop This Flame]]\n | single2date = 9 January 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Celeste''''' is the upcoming self-titled debut album from English singer-songwriter [[Celeste (singer)|Celeste]]. The album was initially planned to be released on September 4, 2020,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title=\u200eCeleste by Celeste|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/celeste/1498436277|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|language=en-us|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> but will be released later due to the physical effects of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"GN\">{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/UKTVLAND/comments/fyrdx7/the_graham_norton_show_s27e01/|title=The Graham Norton Show S27E01|website=UKTVLAND|publisher=Reddit|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=11 April 2020|time=22:56}}</ref> It will include the singles, \"[[Strange (Celeste song)|Strange]]\" and \"[[Stop This Flame]]\".\n\n== Background ==\nCeleste was predicted as a breakthrough act in 2020 by many publications, including ''[[GQ]]'',<ref name=\":30\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/celeste-singer|title=Why Celeste is the most hotly tipped singer for 2020|last=Johnston|first=Kathleen|date=9 January 2020|website=[[GQ]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/best-music-artists-2020|title=Seven musicians to love in 2020|last=Solomon|first=Kate|date=2 January 2020|website=[[GQ]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref> ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/miss-vogue/article/2020-new-musicians|title=9 Musicians Set To Go Global In 2020|last=Collins|first=Hattie|date=20 December 2019|website=[[British Vogue]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|last=Beaumont-Thomas|first=Ben|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/27/bradford-bassline-and-ketamine-charged-punk-50-new-artists-for-2020|title=Bradford bassline and ketamine-charged punk \u2013 50 new artists for 2020|date=27 December 2019|work=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=9 January 2020|url-status=live|last2=Snapes|first2=Laura|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> ''[[NME]]'',<ref name=\"NME100\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/nme-100-essential-new-artists-for-2020-2592024|title=The NME 100: Essential new artists for 2020|last=Smith|first=Thomas|date=3 January 2020|website=[[NME]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref> and ''[[The Independent]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/ones-to-watch-2020-new-music-artists-georgia-celeste-benjiflow-tia-carys-a9259736.html|title=The 10 new artists to look out for in 2020|last=O'Connor|first=Roisin|last2=Pollard|first2=Alexandra|date=31 December 2019|website=[[The Independent]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref> On 9 January 2020, Celeste was announced as the winner of BBC's music poll [[Sound of 2020]].<ref name=\":33\">{{Cite news|last=Savage|first=Mark|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51020113|title=Celeste got fired over her love of music - now she's won the BBC Sound of 2020|date=9 January 2020|work=BBC|access-date=9 January 2020|url-status=live|language=en-GB}}</ref> Following the announcement, she appeared on the [[BBC Breakfast]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wFwJmADiZUg|title=CELESTE BBC Sound of 2020 Winner interview|date=9 January 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> before having her single \"[[Stop This Flame]]\" debuted on [[BBC Radio 1]] by Annie Mac.<ref>{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sounds/play/m000d1ws|title=Radio 1's Future Sounds with Annie Mac - Sound Of 2020: Celeste|date=9 January 2020|last=Mac|first=Annie|type=Radio broadcast|language=en|publisher=[[BBC Sounds]]|minutes=30:18|quote=...I went on BBC Breakfast and I was actually on the news which was so surreal...}}</ref> Her single compilation titled ''Compilation 1.1'' reached No. 1 on the UK's iTunes Chart following her Sound of 2020 win.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.itunescharts.net/uk/artists/music/celeste-2/albums/compilation-11/|title='Compilation 1.1' by Celeste (British Albums iTunes Chart)|website=iTunesCharts.net|url-status=live|access-date=9 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nCeleste was awarded the [[Brit Award for Rising Star|Rising Star Award]] at the [[2020 Brit Awards]],<ref>{{Cite news|last=Snapes|first=Laura|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/06/soul-singer-celeste-named-winner-of-brits-rising-star-award|title=Soul singer Celeste named winner of Brits rising star award|date=6 December 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=11 April 2020|url-status=live|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> where her performance of \"[[Strange (Celeste song)|Strange]]\" caught the attention of other big names in the pop music industry who attended the ceremony such as [[Billie Eilish]],<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1231898771950362624|user=BigTop40|title=So @billieeilish is just as big a fan of @celeste's music are we are|author=The Official Big Top 40|date=24 February 2020}}</ref> [[Camila Cabello|Camilla Cabello]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/CamilaCabelloBR/status/1231949801916375041|title=Camila Cabello Instagram Story: 24 February 2020|url-status=live|access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref> [[Finneas O'Connell|Finneas]],<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1232334740910264322|user=finneas|title=Heard this song for the first time when performing at the brits and fell in love with it immediately|author=FINNEAS|date=25 February 2020}}</ref> and [[Stormzy]].<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1230155489578823680|user=BRITs|title=\"That's a perfect song.\" The moment @stormzy bumped into @celeste backstage at The #BRITs and told her exactly how much he loves 'Strange'|author=BRIT Awards|date=19 February 2020}}</ref> Celeste also performed \"Strange\" on ''[[Later... with Jools Holland]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p07rtsns|title=BBC Two - Later... Live Tracks, Celeste - Strange (Later... With Jools Holland)|website=BBC|language=en-GB|access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref> ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]'',''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sPNnHZk0ai8|title=Celeste: Strange|date=30 January 2020|work=YouTube|publisher=[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]|language=en|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref>'' ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'',''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2020-04-10/graham-norton-show-lockdown/|title=Graham Norton joined by Michael Bubl\u00e9, Michael Sheen, Martin Freeman, Daisy Haggard and Celeste for first lockdown show|last=Fullerton|first=Huw|date=10 April 2020|website=[[Radio Times]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>''<ref name=\"GN\" /> and [[C \u00e0 vous]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.france.tv/france-5/c-a-vous-la-suite/c-a-vous-la-suite-saison-11/1117587-c-a-vous-la-suite.html|title=C \u00e0 vous la suite Int\u00e9grale : Timoth\u00e9e Chalamet, Florence Pugh, Saoirse Ronan et Celeste|work=[[France T\u00e9l\u00e9visions]]|publisher=[[C \u00e0 vous]]|language=fr|access-date=15 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, Celeste told ''[[NME]]'' that she would like the album to be one that people will \"enjoy and listen to for a while\u2013 until at least 2022.\"<ref name=\":32\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OOmOcQwavoU|title=Celeste: Meet the NME 100|date=3 January 2020|work=[[YouTube]]|publisher=NME|language=en|access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref> In April 2020, Celeste told ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'' that the album is likely to be renamed closer to the date of its release.<ref name=\"GN\" /> The album will have 12 tracks in total.<ref name=\":0\" /> Celeste made the front cover of Italian magazine ''[[La Repubblica]]'' in April and told them that the album would also feature the tracks, \"A Kiss\" and \"The Change\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/generale/2020/04/03/news/armonia_celeste-252859049/?awc=15069_1587027836_8d75fa8e4fbdc48db1d6dcedd4d42cd8&source=AWI_DISPLAY|title=Armonia Celeste|last=Ormando|first=Di Lorenzo|date=3 April 2020|website=[[La Repubblica#Supplements and features|Di Repubblica]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> Other unreleased songs that Celeste has performed that are likely to appear on the album are: \"Love is Back\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aI4v9W5KSH8|title=Celeste - Love Is Back (Glastonbury 2019)|date=9 July 2019|website=[[BBC Music]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vo6t21uBleM|title=Celeste - Love is Back (BBC Music Introducing session)|date=4 May 2019|website=[[BBC Music]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fXRAKkLjmaI|title=Celeste live Love is back @ ESNS Stadsschouwburg Groningen 16-01-2020|date=17 January 2020|website=DUTCHess of Rock|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> \"This is Who I Am\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kzw2oVjbVwU|title=This Is Who I Am - Celeste (Fabrique, Milan, 7 December 2019)|last=Keaton|first=Andre D.|date=11 December 2019|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kJDk7Yf0WUk&feature=emb_title|title=Celeste - Live at Omeara, London - 13 Nov 2019|last=Sanders|first=Simon|date=14 November 2019|website=YouTube|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> \"Beloved\"<ref name=\":1\" />.\n\n== Release and promotion ==\nThe album will be released for digital download, CD, signed vinyls and cassette.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://store.universalmusic.com/celeste/|title=Official Celeste Store|website=[[Universal Music]]|url-status=live|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Celeste}}\n\n[[Category:2020 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Upcoming albums]]\n[[Category:Polydor Records albums]]\n[[Category:Celeste (singer) albums]]\n\n{{2020s-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Celeste\n| type         = Studio\n| artist       = [[Celeste (singer)|Celeste]]\n| cover        = Celeste - Celeste.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|09|04|df=yes}}\n| genre        = <!--Please source genre-->\n| length       = \n| label        = [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Jamie Hartman]]|[[John Hill (record producer)|John Hill]]|Barney Lister|Swindle|[[Stephen Wrabel]]}}\n| prev_title   = Lately\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| year         = 2020\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Celeste\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Strange (Celeste song)|Strange]]\n | single1date = 9 April 2019\n | single2     = [[Stop This Flame]]\n | single2date = 9 January 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Celeste''''' is the upcoming self-titled debut album from English singer-songwriter [[Celeste (singer)|Celeste]]. The album was initially planned to be released on September 4, 2020,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title=\u200eCeleste by Celeste|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/celeste/1498436277|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|language=en-us|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> but will be released later due to the physical effects of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"GN\">{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/UKTVLAND/comments/fyrdx7/the_graham_norton_show_s27e01/|title=The Graham Norton Show S27E01|website=UKTVLAND|publisher=Reddit|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=11 April 2020|time=22:56}}</ref> It will include the singles, \"[[Strange (Celeste song)|Strange]]\" and \"[[Stop This Flame]]\".\n\n== Background ==\nCeleste was predicted as a breakthrough act in 2020 by many publications, including ''[[GQ]]'',<ref name=\":30\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/celeste-singer|title=Why Celeste is the most hotly tipped singer for 2020|last=Johnston|first=Kathleen|date=9 January 2020|website=[[GQ]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/best-music-artists-2020|title=Seven musicians to love in 2020|last=Solomon|first=Kate|date=2 January 2020|website=[[GQ]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref> ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/miss-vogue/article/2020-new-musicians|title=9 Musicians Set To Go Global In 2020|last=Collins|first=Hattie|date=20 December 2019|website=[[British Vogue]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|last=Beaumont-Thomas|first=Ben|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/27/bradford-bassline-and-ketamine-charged-punk-50-new-artists-for-2020|title=Bradford bassline and ketamine-charged punk \u2013 50 new artists for 2020|date=27 December 2019|work=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=9 January 2020|url-status=live|last2=Snapes|first2=Laura|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> ''[[NME]]'',<ref name=\"NME100\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/nme-100-essential-new-artists-for-2020-2592024|title=The NME 100: Essential new artists for 2020|last=Smith|first=Thomas|date=3 January 2020|website=[[NME]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref> and ''[[The Independent]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/ones-to-watch-2020-new-music-artists-georgia-celeste-benjiflow-tia-carys-a9259736.html|title=The 10 new artists to look out for in 2020|last=O'Connor|first=Roisin|last2=Pollard|first2=Alexandra|date=31 December 2019|website=[[The Independent]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref> On 9 January 2020, Celeste was announced as the winner of BBC's music poll [[Sound of 2020]].<ref name=\":33\">{{Cite news|last=Savage|first=Mark|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51020113|title=Celeste got fired over her love of music - now she's won the BBC Sound of 2020|date=9 January 2020|work=BBC|access-date=9 January 2020|url-status=live|language=en-GB}}</ref> Following the announcement, she appeared on the [[BBC Breakfast]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wFwJmADiZUg|title=CELESTE BBC Sound of 2020 Winner interview|date=9 January 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> before having her single \"[[Stop This Flame]]\" debuted on [[BBC Radio 1]] by Annie Mac.<ref>{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sounds/play/m000d1ws|title=Radio 1's Future Sounds with Annie Mac - Sound Of 2020: Celeste|date=9 January 2020|last=Mac|first=Annie|type=Radio broadcast|language=en|publisher=[[BBC Sounds]]|minutes=30:18|quote=...I went on BBC Breakfast and I was actually on the news which was so surreal...}}</ref> Her single compilation titled ''Compilation 1.1'' reached No. 1 on the UK's iTunes Chart following her Sound of 2020 win.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.itunescharts.net/uk/artists/music/celeste-2/albums/compilation-11/|title='Compilation 1.1' by Celeste (British Albums iTunes Chart)|website=iTunesCharts.net|url-status=live|access-date=9 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nCeleste was awarded the [[Brit Award for Rising Star|Rising Star Award]] at the [[2020 Brit Awards]],<ref>{{Cite news|last=Snapes|first=Laura|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/06/soul-singer-celeste-named-winner-of-brits-rising-star-award|title=Soul singer Celeste named winner of Brits rising star award|date=6 December 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=11 April 2020|url-status=live|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> where her performance of \"[[Strange (Celeste song)|Strange]]\" caught the attention of other big names in the pop music industry who attended the ceremony such as [[Billie Eilish]],<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1231898771950362624|user=BigTop40|title=So @billieeilish is just as big a fan of @celeste's music are we are|author=The Official Big Top 40|date=24 February 2020}}</ref> [[Camila Cabello|Camilla Cabello]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/CamilaCabelloBR/status/1231949801916375041|title=Camila Cabello Instagram Story: 24 February 2020|url-status=live|access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref> [[Finneas O'Connell|Finneas]],<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1232334740910264322|user=finneas|title=Heard this song for the first time when performing at the brits and fell in love with it immediately|author=FINNEAS|date=25 February 2020}}</ref> and [[Stormzy]].<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1230155489578823680|user=BRITs|title=\"That's a perfect song.\" The moment @stormzy bumped into @celeste backstage at The #BRITs and told her exactly how much he loves 'Strange'|author=BRIT Awards|date=19 February 2020}}</ref> Celeste also performed \"Strange\" on ''[[Later... with Jools Holland]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p07rtsns|title=BBC Two - Later... Live Tracks, Celeste - Strange (Later... With Jools Holland)|website=BBC|language=en-GB|access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref> ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]'',''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sPNnHZk0ai8|title=Celeste: Strange|date=30 January 2020|work=YouTube|publisher=[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]|language=en|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref>'' ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'',''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2020-04-10/graham-norton-show-lockdown/|title=Graham Norton joined by Michael Bubl\u00e9, Michael Sheen, Martin Freeman, Daisy Haggard and Celeste for first lockdown show|last=Fullerton|first=Huw|date=10 April 2020|website=[[Radio Times]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>''<ref name=\"GN\" /> and [[C \u00e0 vous]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.france.tv/france-5/c-a-vous-la-suite/c-a-vous-la-suite-saison-11/1117587-c-a-vous-la-suite.html|title=C \u00e0 vous la suite Int\u00e9grale : Timoth\u00e9e Chalamet, Florence Pugh, Saoirse Ronan et Celeste|work=[[France T\u00e9l\u00e9visions]]|publisher=[[C \u00e0 vous]]|language=fr|access-date=15 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, Celeste told ''[[NME]]'' that she would like the album to be one that people will \"enjoy and listen to for a while\u2013 until at least 2022.\"<ref name=\":32\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OOmOcQwavoU|title=Celeste: Meet the NME 100|date=3 January 2020|work=[[YouTube]]|publisher=NME|language=en|access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref> In April 2020, Celeste told ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]'' that the album is likely to be renamed closer to the date of its release.<ref name=\"GN\" /> The album will have 12 tracks in total.<ref name=\":0\" /> Celeste made the front cover of Italian magazine ''[[La Repubblica]]'' in April and told them that the album would also feature the tracks, \"A Kiss\" and \"The Change\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/generale/2020/04/03/news/armonia_celeste-252859049/?awc=15069_1587027836_8d75fa8e4fbdc48db1d6dcedd4d42cd8&source=AWI_DISPLAY|title=Armonia Celeste|last=Ormando|first=Di Lorenzo|date=3 April 2020|website=[[La Repubblica#Supplements and features|Di Repubblica]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> Other unreleased songs that Celeste has performed that are likely to appear on the album are: \"Love is Back\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aI4v9W5KSH8|title=Celeste - Love Is Back (Glastonbury 2019)|date=9 July 2019|website=[[BBC Music]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vo6t21uBleM|title=Celeste - Love is Back (BBC Music Introducing session)|date=4 May 2019|website=[[BBC Music]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fXRAKkLjmaI|title=Celeste live Love is back @ ESNS Stadsschouwburg Groningen 16-01-2020|date=17 January 2020|website=DUTCHess of Rock|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> \"This is Who I Am\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kzw2oVjbVwU|title=This Is Who I Am - Celeste (Fabrique, Milan, 7 December 2019)|last=Keaton|first=Andre D.|date=11 December 2019|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kJDk7Yf0WUk&feature=emb_title|title=Celeste - Live at Omeara, London - 13 Nov 2019|last=Sanders|first=Simon|date=14 November 2019|website=YouTube|url-status=live|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> \"Beloved\"<ref name=\":1\" />.\n\n== Release and promotion ==\nThe album will be released for digital download, CD, signed vinyls and cassette.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://store.universalmusic.com/celeste/|title=Official Celeste Store|website=[[Universal Music]]|url-status=live|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{2020s-album-stub}}\n{{Celeste}}